    public class SerializationException
extends ComprehensibleException
    Exception signals errors while writting bytes to or reading bytes from a byte containing object such as stream or byte buffer.

      SerializationException(String message, boolean fatal, Object... reasons)
      Creates an exception with a specified message and optional reason varargs where a fatal flag can be set to indicate that the whole read or write process has failed or that only one read or write operation could not be executed and further read/write operations are possible.
      SerializationException(String message, Throwable exception, boolean fatal, Object... reasons)
      Creates an exception with a specified message and optional reason varargs based on an existing exception where a fatal flag can be set to indicate that the whole read or write process has failed or that only one read or write operation could not be executed and further read/write operations are possible.

      • SerializationException

        public SerializationException(String message,
                      boolean fatal,
                      Object... reasons)
        Creates an exception with a specified message and optional reason varargs where a fatal flag can be set to indicate that the whole read or write process has failed or that only one read or write operation could not be executed and further read/write operations are possible.
        Parameters:
        message - the specified exception message
        fatal - true if the whole read/write process failed
        reasons - the optional reasons, which let to the exception

      • SerializationException

        public SerializationException(String message,
                      Throwable exception,
                      boolean fatal,
                      Object... reasons)
        Creates an exception with a specified message and optional reason varargs based on an existing exception where a fatal flag can be set to indicate that the whole read or write process has failed or that only one read or write operation could not be executed and further read/write operations are possible.
        Parameters:
        message - the specified exception message
        exception - the existing exception, which has to be encapsulated
        fatal - true if the whole read/write process failed
        reasons - the optional reasons, which let to the exception
